Trim the root and the dark green leafy part from the @leeks{2}. Halve lengthways then slice widthways. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1} (stalks and all). Shape the @British pork and oregano sausage meat{225%g} into balls (six per person).

> IMPORTANT: Remember to wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with a pinch of @salt{pinch}.

Heat a splash of @oil{1%splash} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. When hot, add the meatballs and cook until browned on the outside and cooked in the middle, ~{9-10%mins}. Turn every couple of mins and lower the heat if they are browning too quickly.

> IMPORTANT: The meatballs are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, add the @spaghetti{200%g} to the pan of boiling water. Cook for ~{6%mins}. Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{}, pop back in the pan and drizzle with @oil{1%splash} to stop it sticking together.

Once the meatballs are cooked, use a #slotted spoon{} to remove them from the pan to a #plate{}. Put the pan back on medium-high heat and add a drizzle of @oil{1%splash} if it's dry. Add the leeks with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @ground black pepper{pinch}. Stir and cook until softened, ~{6-7%mins}. Add the garlic and @wholegrain mustard{1}, stir and cook for ~{1%minute} more. Pour in the @water for the sauce{200%ml} and stir in the @chicken stock powder{1}. Add the meatballs back into the pan.

Cover the pan with a #lid{} or some #foil{}, reduce the heat to medium-low and simmer for ~{5%mins}, then remove the lid from the pan and stir in the @unsalted butter{15%g} and the @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g} until melted. Remove from the heat, taste and add @salt{} and @ground black pepper{} if you feel it needs it.

Add the wheat spaghetti to the sauce and meatballs along with half the parsley. Toss together to combine and add a splash of @?water{1%splash} if it's a little dry. Serve in #bowls{} with the @feta cheese{50%g} crumbled on top and a sprinkling of remaining parsley. Enjoy!